http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Free-coaching-for-poor-students/article14002582.ece

The Police Department has offered free coaching for the ensuing Group II and police constable tests to those aspirants who belong to below poverty line economic category. The coaching for written tests and physical tests will start on January 21. Aspirants should appear for the selection at the AR headquarters in Adilabad town at 10 a.m. on January 18 with Aadhaar card, white ration card, caste certificate and SSC, Intermediate and Degree certificates. About 200 men would be trained at Adilabad while 100 men and 100 women would be trained at Nirmal, according to a press release here on Saturday.